A couple of years ago I had a discussion at work with a group of other people about whether the sound quality of a vinyl record was different on the outer most range and the inner most range.
This is a topic that the world cannot be without so I decided to write a blog post on this.

### Analog sound encoding

(Tegning)


1. Fortæl om analog encoding af lyd
2. Vis at jo mere plads, desto flere detaljer
3. Vis så at rotationshastigheden er den samme yderst som inderst på en gramofonplade
4. Rul nu gramofonpladen ud og påpege at der er forskellig længde. Jf punkt 2, er der dermed også dårligere kvalitet inderst.
5. Referer til wiki der beskriver problemet: https://www.yoursoundmatters.com/vinyl-record-inner-groove-distortion-simple-explanation/#:~:text=Inner%2Dgroove%20distortion%20is%20an,part%20of%20the%20vinyl%20experience.